.head 3 +  Function: GetStrJulianDate !__Exported
.head 4 -  Description:
.head 4 +  Returns
.head 5 -  String: !__Exported
.head 4 +  Parameters
.head 5 -  Date/Time: dtDate !__Exported
.head 4 -  Static Variables
.head 4 -  Local variables
.head 4 +  Actions
.head 5 -  Return SalNumberToStrX( dtDate - SalDateYearBegin( dtDate ) + 1, 0 ) || SalStrMidX( SalNumberToStrX( SalDateYear( dtDate ), 0 ), 3, 1 )
.head 3 +  Function: DateMonthEnd !__Exported
.head 4 -  Description: Returns the last day of the month given in date/time field
.head 4 +  Returns
.head 5 -  Date/Time: !__Exported
.head 4 +  Parameters
.head 5 -  Date/Time: dtGivenDate !__Exported
.head 4 -  Static Variables
.head 4 +  Local variables
.head 5 -  Date/Time: dtTmpDate !__Exported
.head 5 -  Number: nDay !__Exported
.head 5 -  Number: nMonth !__Exported
.head 5 -  Number: nYear !__Exported
.head 4 +  Actions
.head 5 -  Set nDay = SalDateDay( dtGivenDate )
.head 5 -  Set nMonth = SalDateMonth( dtGivenDate )
.head 5 +  If nMonth < 12
.head 6 -  Set nMonth = nMonth + 1
.head 5 +  Else
.head 6 -  Set nMonth = 1
.head 5 -  Set nYear = SalDateYear( dtGivenDate )
.head 5 -  Set dtTmpDate = SalDateConstruct( nYear, nMonth, nDay, 0, 0, 0 )
.head 5 -  Set dtTmpDate = SalDateMonthBegin( dtTmpDate ) - 1
.head 5 -  Return dtTmpDate
.head 3 +  Function: SubtractMonthsFromMonth !__Exported
.head 4 -  Description: Assumes the first parameter is a month and the second is the number
of months to subtract.  month parameter is assumed to be in the
month range 1..12 and NO range checking is performed
.head 4 +  Returns
.head 5 -  Number: !__Exported
.head 4 +  Parameters
.head 5 -  Number: nMonth !__Exported
.head 5 -  Number: nSubMonths !__Exported
.head 4 -  Static Variables
.head 4 +  Local variables
.head 5 -  Number: nCount !__Exported
.head 4 +  Actions
.head 5 -  Set nCount = nSubMonths
.head 5 +  While nCount > 0
.head 6 -  Set nMonth = nMonth - 1
.head 6 -  Set nCount = nCount - 1
.head 6 +  If nMonth < 1
.head 7 -  Set nMonth = 12
.head 5 -  Return nMonth
.head 3 +  Function: DaysDiffBetweenMonths !__Exported
.head 4 -  Description:
.head 4 +  Returns
.head 5 -  Number: !__Exported
.head 4 +  Parameters
.head 5 -  Number: nFirstMonth !__Exported
.head 5 -  Number: nSecondMonth !__Exported
.head 4 -  Static Variables
.head 4 +  Local variables
.head 5 -  Number: nMonths !__Exported
.head 4 +  Actions
.head 5 +  If nFirstMonth < nSecondMonth
.head 6 -  Set nMonths = nSecondMonth - nFirstMonth
.head 5 +  Else If nFirstMonth = nSecondMonth
.head 6 -  Set nMonths = 0
.head 5 +  Else
.head 6 -  Set nMonths = nFirstMonth - nSecondMonth
.head 5 -  Return nMonths
.head 3 +  Function: OurDateYear !__Exported
.head 4 -  Description: Because SqlWindows 3.0 SalDateYear returned a 2 digit year. eg 94
and SqlWindows 5.0 SalDateYear returns 1994 our database has
year fields as keys and we cannot change them, this function
takes the 1900 of the year if its not year 1997 or more.  Assumption
is that after year 1997 we will want to have 1997, 1998, 1999, 2000 etc 
year fields in the database.
.head 4 +  Returns
.head 5 -  Number: !__Exported
.head 4 +  Parameters
.head 5 -  Date/Time: dtCurrentDate !__Exported
.head 4 -  Static Variables
.head 4 +  Local variables
.head 5 -  Number: nCurrentYear !__Exported
.head 4 +  Actions
.head 5 -  Set nCurrentYear = SalDateYear( dtCurrentDate )
.head 5 +  If nCurrentYear < 1997
.head 6 -  Set nCurrentYear = nCurrentYear - 1900
.head 5 -  Return nCurrentYear
.head 3 +  Function: AdjustYearToYearOfSale !__Exported
.head 4 -  Description:
.head 4 -  Returns
.head 4 +  Parameters
.head 5 -  Receive Number: nYear !__Exported
.head 4 -  Static Variables
.head 4 -  Local variables
.head 4 +  Actions
.head 5 +  If nYear < 1997 AND nYear > 1900
.head 6 -  Set nYear = nYear - 1900
.head 5 +  Else If nYear > 96 AND nYear < 100
.head 6 -  Set nYear = nYear + 1900
.head 5 +  Else If nYear >= 0 AND nYear < 50
.head 6 -  Set nYear = nYear + 2000
.head 3 +  Function: AdjustYearOfSaleToYear !__Exported
.head 4 -  Description:
.head 4 -  Returns
.head 4 +  Parameters
.head 5 -  Receive Number: nYear !__Exported
.head 4 -  Static Variables
.head 4 -  Local variables
.head 4 +  Actions
.head 5 +  If nYear < 100 AND nYear >= 50
.head 6 -  Set nYear = nYear + 1900
.head 5 +  Else If nYear >= 0 AND nYear < 50
.head 6 -  Set nYear = nYear + 2000
.head 3 +  Function: GetUniqueCurrentSysDT !__Exported
.head 4 -  Description:
.head 4 +  Returns
.head 5 -  Date/Time: !__Exported
.head 4 -  Parameters
.head 4 +  Static Variables
.head 5 -  Date/Time: dtLastSysDT !__Exported
.head 4 +  Local variables
.head 5 -  Date/Time: dtSysDT !__Exported
.head 4 +  Actions
.head 5 -  Set dtSysDT = SalDateCurrent(  )
.head 5 +  While dtSysDT = dtLastSysDT
.head 6 -  Set dtSysDT = SalDateCurrent(  )
.head 5 -  Set dtLastSysDT = dtSysDT
.head 5 -  Return dtSysDT
